Broadcaster and political analyst Oliver Dickson has joined SA FM, one of the biggest talk radio stations in the country. Dickson, a former director at Home Affairs, will host a weekly current affairs show starting today at 6pm to 7pm. He shared that he had always wanted to work for SA FM and that he hoped he can play a role in the democratic functioning of public broadcasting. “I’ve always wanted to work for the public broadcaster because I’m a firm believer in what it is meant to achieve,” wrote Dickson.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.